rip, shit or bust
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:as an asseveration or attrib, of action or person who goes bull-at-a-gate at anything without thought to the consequences, or the quality of the result. -->ca1930 Havelock. -->ca1940 (Les Cleveland)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also: rip, shit and bust.
